backing dog
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a dog used to clear congestion of sheep in a gateway, race or into a pen by running along the backs of sheep; a dog trained to help move yarded sheep by running across their backs.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See: back v.
Pronunciation:
